# Versioning

The single source of truth for the version is the `version` field in
`pyproject.toml` (re-exported as `app.__version__`). The footer renders
it, so every bump is visible to users.

## When to bump

Bump the version whenever you make a significant change: a new feature,
a user-facing behaviour change, a bug fix, or a notable refactor. Skip
the bump only for trivial edits (typos, comments, formatting, internal
docs).

Do the bump in the same change that introduces the work, so the deployed
version always reflects what is running.

## How to bump

While the version carries a `-beta.N` suffix (currently
`6.0.0-beta.N`), only increment the beta number:

- `6.0.0-beta.1` -> `6.0.0-beta.2`

After the `6.0.0` release (suffix dropped), follow semantic versioning:

- Patch (`6.0.0` -> `6.0.1`) for bug fixes and small changes.
- Minor (`6.0.0` -> `6.1.0`) for new, backward-compatible features.
